# Reticle environment — copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit .env (it is gitignored).
# Only the license vars below are meaningful to Reticle today; add app vars as needed.

# ─── Enterprise licensing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Reticle verifies enterprise (ee/) features OFFLINE with Ed25519 — nothing phones home.

# CUSTOMER side — the signed key Reticle issues you. Set this to activate enterprise
# features in production. Format: base64url(payload).base64url(signature).
# Check status any time with: reticle license
RETICLE_LICENSE_KEY=

# RELEASE side — the issuer PUBLIC key (spki PEM), baked into a release build so it
# can verify customer keys. Safe to store openly; it can only verify, never mint.
# When unset, Reticle runs in eval mode (enterprise features free, no enforcement).
RETICLE_LICENSE_PUBLIC_KEY=

# ISSUER side — Reticle ONLY. The signing PRIVATE key (pkcs8 PEM). NEVER put the real
# value here or in any committed file — load it at sign time from a secret manager:
#   RETICLE_LICENSE_PRIVATE_KEY="$(op read 'op://Vault/reticle-issuer/private.pem')" \
#     node scripts/issue-license.mjs sign --org "Acme Corp" --plan enterprise --days 365
# Anyone holding this can mint unlimited licenses — its leak breaks the whole model.
RETICLE_LICENSE_PRIVATE_KEY=
